                            {
                              "type": "frame",
                              "id": "rpIKF",
                              "name": "prdBodyA rendered markdown",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "layout": "vertical",
                              "gap": 24,
                              "children": [
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "wbWC3",
                                  "name": "h1 MVP Plan LocalLens",
                                  "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "MVP Plan: LocalLens",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.05,
                                  "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                  "fontSize": 34,
                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "JFepM",
                                  "name": "document metadata",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "fill": "#FAFAFA",
                                  "stroke": {
                                    "thickness": 1,
                                    "fill": "#E5E5E5"
                                  },
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 6,
                                  "padding": [
                                    14,
                                    16
                                  ],
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "ypBIN",
                                      "name": "metadata text",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "Created: 2024-01-15\nStatus: Draft\nPRD Reference: Product Requirements Document: LocalLens\nTarget MVP Duration: 6 weeks",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.45,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "Hb3Zn",
                                  "name": "I MVP Overview",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "nmNxY",
                                      "name": "h2 MVP Overview",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "I. MVP Overview",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "b6rtC",
                                      "name": "overview body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "1.1 Product Vision Summary\nLocalLens is a community-driven travel platform that connects solo travelers with authentic local experiences through custom itineraries curated by verified residents. The platform eliminates tourist traps by providing genuine insider knowledge for meaningful cultural immersion.\n\n1.2 MVP Hypothesis\nWe believe that solo travelers aged 25-35 want verified local recommendations for authentic experiences beyond mainstream tourist attractions. We will know we are right when 70% of MVP users complete their purchased itinerary and rate the authenticity as 4+ stars.\n\n1.3 Problem Being Validated\nSolo travelers consistently end up at overcrowded tourist attractions despite seeking authentic experiences because existing platforms lack verified local curation and hyperlocal discovery capabilities.\n\n1.4 Target User Segment\nPrimary user: solo travelers aged 25-35 seeking authentic cultural experiences.\nUser context: planning trips to new destinations with 3-7 day stays.\nSuccess looks like: completing locally curated itineraries that feel authentic and Instagram-worthy.\n\n1.5 MVP Scope Boundaries\nIn scope: basic registration, simple curator verification, static itinerary generation, one-time payment processing, mobile-responsive web app, Google Maps integration, basic search/filtering.\nOut of scope: advanced personalization, community validation, real-time messaging, revenue sharing dashboard, native mobile apps, offline maps, AI-powered recommendations.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "ftcbb",
                                  "name": "II Core MVP Features",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "GwOKy",
                                      "name": "h2 Core MVP Features",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "II. Core MVP Features",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "EuIor",
                                      "name": "features body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "2.1 Feature Summary\nMVP-001 User Registration & Profiles: account creation and preference storage. Priority P1.\nMVP-002 Curator Verification System: ensures local authenticity. Priority P1.\nMVP-003 Itinerary Generation: core value delivery mechanism. Priority P1.\nMVP-004 Payment Processing: revenue generation. Priority P1.\nMVP-005 Maps Integration: location visualization and navigation. Priority P1.\n\n2.2 Feature Details\nMVP-001 User Registration & Profiles\nDescription: email/password account creation plus travel preference collection for destination types, budget range, and experience interests.\nAcceptance criteria: users can register, set 3-5 preference categories, see purchase history, reset passwords, and verify email before activation. Complexity S.\n\nMVP-002 Curator Verification System\nDescription: local residents submit proof of residency and create curator profiles with recommendation submission.\nAcceptance criteria: curator applications include location and proof; admin can approve/reject; verified curators submit recommendations with photos; profiles show verification; recommendation form includes title, description, and location. Complexity M.\n\nMVP-003 Itinerary Generation\nDescription: matches destination and preferences with curator recommendations to create 6-8 location itineraries with basic routing.\nAcceptance criteria: destination/date input, 6-8 recommendations, chronological route, descriptions/photos/locations, walking times, and PDF download. Complexity L.\n\nMVP-004 Payment Processing\nDescription: Stripe one-time payments with $15-30 pricing tiers and order management.\nAcceptance criteria: secure Stripe payment form, multiple tiers, confirmation and receipt, purchase history, failed payment retry. Complexity M.\n\nMVP-005 Maps Integration\nDescription: Google Maps display for itinerary locations, routing, and location details.\nAcceptance criteria: interactive map, clickable markers, routing, addresses/opening hours, and mobile-optimized interface. Complexity M.\n\n2.3 Explicitly Excluded Features\nReal-time messaging, community ratings, curator revenue sharing dashboard, push notifications, and offline map downloads move to Phase 2 or Phase 3.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "CVLMA",
                                  "name": "III User Flow",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "e4SPK",
                                      "name": "h2 User Flow",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "III. User Flow",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "ex0MP",
                                      "name": "flow body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "3.1 Primary User Journey\nSolo Traveler -> Discovers Platform -> Creates Account -> Inputs Trip Details -> Purchases Itinerary -> Explores Destinations -> Shares Experience.\n\n3.2 Step-by-Step Flow\nEntry & Onboarding\n1. Landing Page: user discovers LocalLens through search/referral, then sees a clear value proposition and sample itinerary preview.\n2. Registration: user creates an email account and sets basic travel preferences such as urban/nature, budget, and interests.\n\nCore Experience\n3. Trip Planning: user inputs destination and travel dates; system shows available curated itinerary previews.\n4. Itinerary Selection: user reviews recommendations and sees curator profiles plus authenticity signals.\n5. Purchase: user completes payment and immediately accesses the full itinerary with maps.\n\nValue Delivery\n6. Trip Execution: user navigates to locations with integrated maps and experiences authentic local spots with cultural context.\n\n3.3 Critical Path\nLanding Page -> Sign Up -> Set Preferences -> Input Destination -> View Itinerary Preview -> Complete Purchase -> Download Itinerary -> Navigate & Explore.\n\n3.4 Edge Cases\nNo curators in destination: show Coming Soon with email notification signup.\nPayment failure: show clear error, retry, and support contact.\nInsufficient curator recommendations: combine multiple curator inputs or reduce itinerary length.\nMaps API failure: fall back to static maps and address information.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "xB2lc",
                                  "name": "IV Tech Stack",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "lTyhh",
                                      "name": "h2 Tech Stack",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "IV. Tech Stack & Tool Recommendations",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "GXotc",
                                      "name": "tech body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "4.1 Recommended Stack Overview\nFrontend: Next.js. Alternative: React + Vite. Rationale: full-stack framework with SSR for SEO.\nBackend: Next.js API Routes. Alternative: Node.js + Express. Rationale: unified codebase and faster development.\nDatabase: PostgreSQL. Alternative: MongoDB. Rationale: relational user/curator data.\nHosting: Vercel. Alternative: AWS. Rationale: seamless Next.js deployment and scaling.\nAuth: NextAuth.js. Alternative: Auth0. Rationale: built-in Next.js integration.\n\n4.2 Frontend\nNext.js 14 for full-stack React, Tailwind CSS + Headless UI for rapid accessible components, React Query + Zustand for server/client state.\n\n4.3 Backend\nNext.js API Routes with REST endpoints for a simple MVP implementation.\n\n4.4 Database\nPostgreSQL on Neon for serverless Postgres; Redis on Upstash for sessions and API caching.\n\n4.5 Infrastructure\nVercel hosting with automatic scaling/global CDN, plus GitHub Actions + Vercel CI/CD.\n\n4.6 Third-Party Services\nNextAuth.js for authentication, Stripe for payments, Resend for email, Google Maps for location services, PostHog for analytics, Cloudinary for image uploads.\n\n4.7 No-Code / Low-Code Alternatives\nBubble for full app development, Webflow + Airtable for frontend/database, Supabase for backend-as-a-service. Trade-offs include speed versus customization, scaling, and lock-in.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "lH3Lq",
                                  "name": "V AI Automation",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "Mpj7k",
                                      "name": "h2 AI Automation",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "V. AI Automation Suggestions",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "WUotJ",
                                      "name": "ai body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "5.1 AI-Assisted Development\nCode generation: GitHub Copilot can autocomplete React components and API routes, saving roughly 40% development time.\nUI design: v0.dev can generate Tailwind components from descriptions, saving roughly 60% frontend styling.\nAPI development: ChatGPT-4 can draft schemas and endpoint logic, saving roughly 30% backend setup.\nTesting: GitHub Copilot can generate tests and test data, saving roughly 50% testing time.\n\n5.2 AI-Powered Product Features\nItinerary matching: GPT-4 API matches user preferences to curator recommendations with context-aware scoring.\nContent moderation: OpenAI Moderation reviews curator submissions for inappropriate content.\nRecommendation descriptions: GPT-4 enhances curator descriptions with cultural context and travel tips.\n\n5.3 Automation Workflows\nCurator verification: Zapier + Google Sheets automate verification emails and status tracking.\nPayment notifications: Stripe webhooks + Resend generate receipts and itinerary delivery.\nContent enhancement: GPT-4 API improves recommendation descriptions with local context.\n\n5.4 Practical Examples\nItinerary generation: user preferences plus curator recommendations produce an optimized schedule with routing and cultural context. Manual curation drops from 4 hours to 30 minutes.\nRecommendation enhancement: basic name/location/description plus Google Places data produces enhanced hours, price range, and cultural significance. Manual research drops from 1 hour to 2 minutes.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "AvP8O",
                                  "name": "VI Timeline Milestones",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "okmBo",
                                      "name": "h2 Timeline",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "VI. Timeline & Milestones",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "dPNEe",
                                      "name": "timeline body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "6.1 Overview Timeline\nPhase 1, week 1: Setup & Design.\nPhase 2, weeks 2-4: Core Development.\nPhase 3, week 5: Testing & Integration.\nPhase 4, week 6: Launch & Feedback.\n\n6.2 Milestone Details\nMilestone 1: Setup & Design, 1 week. Objectives: establish development environment, create UI design system and flows, configure Stripe and Google Maps. Deliverables include Next.js setup, database connection, Tailwind component library, API integrations, wireframes, and staging. Exit: tools configured and basic app renders.\n\nMilestone 2: Core Feature Development, 3 weeks. Objectives: build the five MVP features, authentication/data models, and admin curator management. Effort: registration 3 days, curator system 5 days, itinerary generation 8 days, payments 4 days, maps 3 days. Exit: all features work in staging with test data.\n\nMilestone 3: Testing & Integration, 1 week. Objectives: test user flows and payments, optimize performance, harden security, prepare content. Testing includes Jest + React Testing Library, payment/maps manual testing, 5-user purchase-flow testing, and OWASP checklist. Exit: critical paths tested and no blocking bugs.\n\nMilestone 4: Launch & Feedback, 1 week. Objectives: production deployment, monitoring, soft launch, feedback collection. Deliverables: production live, 50 registered users, 10 itinerary purchases, initial feedback and metrics.\n\n6.3 Resources\nFull-stack developer full-time for phases 1-4; UI/UX designer part-time 20 hrs/week for phases 1-2; product manager part-time 15 hrs/week for phases 1-4.\n\n6.4 Dependencies & Risks\nGoogle Maps API limits, Stripe complexity, curator content availability, and user acquisition. Mitigations: usage monitoring and caching, tested payment libraries, seeded team content, and personal/social acquisition.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "Nyfku",
                                  "name": "VII Metrics Validation",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "ngal3",
                                      "name": "h2 Metrics",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "VII. Success Metrics & Validation",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "0pzzb",
                                      "name": "metrics body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "7.1 MVP Success Criteria\nUser registration: 50 users, measured in PostHog.\nPurchase conversion: 20% of registered users, measured in Stripe.\nItinerary completion: 70% of purchases, measured by feedback survey.\nAuthenticity rating: 4+ star average, measured by post-trip survey.\nCurator applications: 15 verified curators, measured in admin dashboard.\n\n7.2 Validation Signals\nStrong positive signal: greater than 25% conversion, 4.5+ authenticity ratings, organic word-of-mouth referrals.\nWeak signal: 15-20% conversion, 3.5-4.0 star ratings, partial itinerary completion.\nNegative signal: below 10% conversion, below 3.5 star ratings, high refund requests.\n\n7.3 Post-MVP Decision Framework\nMetrics exceeded: scale to 10 destinations and add P1 features like messaging and reviews.\nMetrics met: optimize conversion flow, expand curator base, and iterate on feedback.\nMetrics not met: analyze feedback, adjust pricing, or consider a pivot to booking platform.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "qwNbF",
                                  "name": "VIII Open Questions",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "layout": "vertical",
                                  "gap": 12,
                                  "children": [
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "GSXZP",
                                      "name": "h2 Open Questions",
                                      "fill": "#0A0A0A",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "VIII. Open Questions & Assumptions",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.1,
                                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                                      "fontSize": 26,
                                      "fontWeight": "700"
                                    },
                                    {
                                      "type": "text",
                                      "id": "bkpho",
                                      "name": "questions body",
                                      "fill": "#444444",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "8.1 Assumptions\nSolo travelers will pay $15-30 for curated local recommendations.\nLocal residents will contribute content for revenue sharing opportunities.\nMobile-responsive web app is sufficient for validation; native app is not needed.\nManual curator verification scales for MVP volume below 50 curators.\n\n8.2 Open Questions\nOQ-001: What revenue split motivates curator participation? Impact high. Status: needs clarification.\nOQ-002: How many recommendations are needed per itinerary? Impact medium. Status: needs clarification.\nOQ-003: Should MVP include booking integration? Impact medium. Status: needs clarification.\n\n8.3 Decisions Needed Before Development\nPricing model: $15/$25/$30 tiers versus single price. Deadline week 1.\nCurator revenue share: 30%, 50%, or 70% split. Deadline week 1.\nGeographic focus: 3-5 major cities versus single city. Deadline week 1.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 13,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
                                  ]
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ]
                        },
